        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 20 at 3:48PM MDT until July 20 at 4:45PM MDT by NWS Glasgow MT</headline>
        <description>SVRGGW

The National Weather Service in Glasgow has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
East central Garfield County in northeastern Montana...
Southwestern McCone County in northeastern Montana...
Northwestern Prairie County in northeastern Montana...

* Until 445 PM MDT.

* At 347 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Jordan,
moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...70 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect considerable tree damage. Damage is likely to
mobile homes, roofs, and outbuildings.

* Locations impacted include...
Circle, Jordan, Flowing Wells Rest Area, Nelson Creek Rec Area,
Brockway, Watkins, and Van Norman.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
